Fix broken unittests in Python 2.7.

Originally all test classes were decorated by going over the class via
inspection - however, this doesn't work in Python 2.7 because the
methods that are returned from getmembers are all unbound (in Python 3+,
this is fixed as all methods are just function objects).

Now this uses a metaclass with six to work in both Python 2 and 3.
Add PyPI classifiers and additional metadata.

Releasing 0.5.1.

Includes fixes for the following issues:
* #33: Update requests_oauthlib from 0.5.0 -> 0.6.1
* #34: Add LICENSE
* #35: Add supported versions of python
* #38: Fix broken tests in Python 2.7 due to class decorating with
  responses.activate.

Fix new version script and versioning for setup.py.

* Version is no longer in its own file, but now exists in __init__.py
* Version is pulled into setup.py via reading __init__.py and parsing
  via regex (the re module will always be installed, and it avoids
  importing 3rd party dependencies).
* Deploy script now modifiys the version in __init__.py.
* Added additional metadata to the package.
Fix tests and README due to versioning changes.
